# This file tells git (the tool that saves versions of your work) which
# files to keep private and NOT share. You almost never need to edit it.

# Your secret keys. NEVER share this file. This keeps it private.
# (The .env.example file is safe and IS shared, it's just a template.)
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# Your personal, private notes (if you ever make a CLAUDE.local.md)
CLAUDE.local.md

# Local progress tracking for the /start-here guide
.start-here-state.json

# Files your computer creates automatically (you can ignore these)
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# Editor settings
.vscode/*
!.vscode/extensions.json
